# Core Engineering Standards

- Keep changes small and focused on the user's request.
- Preserve existing behavior unless the task explicitly asks for changes.
- Avoid introducing new dependencies unless clearly necessary.
- Reuse existing patterns in this repo before creating new abstractions.
- Run relevant checks after edits (`pnpm lint`, then build if needed).
- If a change affects UI behavior, include brief manual verification steps.
